# DEPTH4 global writing — retail voice constitution

**Product:** thesis engine for **unpriced scenarios** and **how evidence moves probability over time**.

**Code source of truth (keep in sync):**

- `signal/apps/web/src/lib/thesis-engine-v2/depth4-retail-voice-constitution.ts` — `DEPTH4_RETAIL_VOICE_TEST`, `DEPTH4_RETAIL_VOICE_CONSTITUTION_FOR_LLM` (injected into macro LLM system prompts).
- `signal/apps/web/src/lib/thesis-engine-v2/thesis-book-template.ts` — thesis book snippet + Supabase `body` JSON rules.
- `signal/apps/web/src/lib/macro-reasoning/prompts.ts` — macro / promoted narrative prompts.

This applies to **everything user-facing** DEPTH4 writes or displays: thesis titles, micro-labels, body sections, L1–L4, scenarios, market edge / what’s unpriced, trigger / trade / invalidation / time stop, feed teasers, promoted narratives, drawer summaries, assistant summaries, assessment / risk, **and any fallback or mock string**.

---

## 1) Canonical voice

- Short, direct, human, plain; readable in ~3 seconds.
- What is happening, why it matters, and (in Trade plan / execution blocks) optional framing of actions — **thesis hero** copy is a **market forecast**, not buy/sell advice.
- Sharp market headline or trader note for a **smart non-professional**.
- **Not:** hedge-fund memo, bank strategist note, consultant deck, placeholder template, internal product copy.

---

## 2) DEPTH4 RETAIL VOICE TEST (do not use “Iran-style” shorthand)

Before finalizing any user-facing line, ask:

1. Could a smart retail trader understand this instantly?
2. Does it sound like a clear market headline, not a PM memo?
3. Does it say what happened / why it matters (and, where appropriate, trade-plan context) in plain words — without imperative Buy/Sell on thesis hero surfaces?
4. Does it avoid hedge-fund or consultant vocabulary?
5. Could it be read aloud naturally without sounding robotic?

If any answer is **no**, rewrite.

---

## 3) Language — prefer / avoid

**Prefer:** “money is still expensive”, “the stock still trades like…”, “the market is missing…”, “a few winners carry the story”, “owning the whole index hides the cracks”, “contracts lock in future work”, “future work pipeline”, profits, margins, cash flow, debt, weaker names, small caps, wait, trim, stand down — and **forecast phrasing** on thesis heroes (“X will underperform…”, “Y will stay bid…”).

**Thesis hero / title / one-line / feed headline:** never imperative **Buy**, **Sell**, **Go long**, **Go short**, **Don't buy**, **Don't add**, **Add exposure**, **Reduce exposure**. Trade plan fields may still use Enter / Trim / etc. under the product disclaimer.

**Avoid or replace** (unless defined in plain words in the same sentence): dispersion, index diversification, basket repricing / reprices cleanly, convexity, beta, duration, regime, setup (trade noun), expression (jargon), book bias, equity books, **variant read / variant perception**, sell-side models, backlog math, cash conversion, conversion quality, time compression, flow story, and any sentence that sounds like a hedge-fund note.

Say **“the edge”** or **“what the market hasn’t priced yet”** — not “variant read.”

---

## 4) One job per block

- **Micro-label:** 3–6 words; human; memorable; no ticker; no jargon.
- **Hero title:** only full thesis sentence — `[Asset] will [direction + move] because [plain cause], within [time window].` (No Buy/Sell imperatives.)
- **One-line summary:** optional hook; not a duplicate hero.
- **L1–L4:** facts → near window → year payout → 2026 backdrop; plain language; one main new idea per level (see thesis book + QQQ exemplar).
- **What’s unpriced:** the edge, **once**.
- **Trigger / trade / invalidation / time stop:** each **once**, observable.
- **Why thesis exists:** framing only; do not repeat hero / edge / trade blocks.
- **Risk factors:** new words; never paste invalidation again.
- **Scenarios:** thesis-specific; name **asset + driver**. **Banned** generic lines: “Trend continues with noisy headlines”, “Catalyst confirms direction early”, “Base trade plan remains operative”, “Invalidation triggers hit”, “Accelerated path to targets.”

Do **not** repeat the same sentence or idea across blocks.

---

## 5) Feed / scan layer

Feed is a **scan** layer: headline → strengthens or weakens a thesis → open if you care. Short teaser only; **no** thesis paragraphs in feed fields.

---

## 6) QQQ / AI capex as structural template

Every catalog thesis uses the **same** ladder and retail bar as the QQQ AI-cost template — see `DEPTH4_THESIS_BOOK_SNIPPET_FOR_LLM` for the canonical `thesisCascade` shape and anti-patterns.

---

## 7) Six checks (every thesis)

1. **Forecast** in plain English: asset first, then **will** + move (underperform, rerate higher, stay bid, fall, …), then because + window — not vague “avoid”, and **not** imperative Buy/Sell on the hero line.
2. Specific future event.
3. Plain cause (define “AI-related spending (chips, data centers, staff)” etc. once).
4. Time-bound window or catalyst.
5. L1–L4 cascade (book page) or event `reasoning_chain` (promoted narrative) — both retail-only.
6. What the market misses — the edge, plain words.

---

## 8) Display title & statement

`[Asset] will [direction + move] because [plain cause] [within time window]` — optional trailing `, probability [N%]` in `thesis_statement` / detail copy.

**Banned on this surface:** Buy, Sell, Go long, Go short, Don’t buy, Don’t add, Add exposure, Reduce exposure.

---

## 9) Four-level reasoning — two surfaces

### A) Thesis page — `thesisCascade` on `Thesis`

| Level | Job |
|-------|-----|
| **L1** | Facts now only |
| **L2** | Watch this week / quarter |
| **L3** | How the trade pays this year for the named asset |
| **L4** | 2026 backdrop for all DEPTH4 work |

### B) Promoted event — `reasoning_chain` in macro JSON

Uses LEVEL 1–4 headers per `prompts.ts` contract; same retail voice and banned list.

**Implementation:** `reasoning_chain` exact headers; `impacted_assets` with `L2 — TLT` style prefixes; `mispricing_hypothesis` often L3–L4.

---

## 10) Time horizon

**Allowed:** days–2w event; 2w–3mo trend; 3–6mo with near-term proof.  
**Banned:** “eventually”, multi-year-only without a catalyst, vague long-term value.  
**Required:** window or dated catalyst; proof within **six months**.

---

## 11) Event narrative & UI

- **Thesis trade line:** full retail **forecast** sentence + when + probability (same ban as hero — no Buy/Sell imperatives).
- **Trade implication:** exactly **Bullish** OR **Bearish** OR **Neutral**; tickers; **bias and what to watch** (avoid imperative buy/sell/add on thesis-facing lines; use “bias”, “pressure”, “watch [print]”).
- **Relation chips:** sentence case; no raw **adjacent** enum shown as a harsh pill (see product notes in codebase).

**Brand tokens (UI):** accent `#E8473F`, background `#111110`, text `#ffffff` / `#888888`.

---

## 12) Final QA before ship

- Sounds like DEPTH4, not a mock?
- Retail trader gets it in one pass?
- No leftover internal / banned jargon?
- No block so generic it could fit any thesis?
- No duplicate sentence across the same page?

---

## 13) Never mention the machinery

No LLM, model, Claude, Opus, or “AI-generated” in user-facing copy — present as **DEPTH4**.
